# Installing WSL (Windows Subsystem for Linux) â€“ Windows 11

This guide explains how to install **WSL 2** and **Ubuntu** on **Windows 11**.  
WSL allows you to run a Linux environment directly on Windows, without using a full virtual machine.

---

# Goal

After completing this installation, you will be able to:
- use a Linux terminal (Ubuntu)
- compile and run code
- use tools like Git, Python, Node.js, Docker, etc.
- work in an environment similar to real Linux servers

---

# Requirements

- Windows 11 (version 22H2 or newer)
- **Administrator** privileges
- Virtualization enabled in BIOS/UEFI

ðŸ‘‰ To check virtualization status:  
Task Manager â†’ **Performance** â†’ **CPU** â†’ *Virtualization: Enabled*

---

# Automatic Installation

## Open PowerShell as Administrator
- Right-click on the **Start** menu
- Select **Terminal (Adm**

## Run the installation command (on Powershell)
```
wsl --install
```
## Restart your computer
The restart is required!

## Verify the installation
Run the next command on Powershell
```
wsl --status
```
You should see Ubuntu running with WSL 2.

